ioning will find SOME way to fail even if a great guru or god a=\r\nre ready to help.\n=A0\n*=A0=A0=A0=A0=A0=A0=A0 *=A0=A0=A0=A0=A0=A0=A0 *\n=A0\nN=\r\now, the question is: How do we reduce our conditioning? Unfortunately, ther=\r\ne is no single magic bullet. Thinking of a god, mantras, bhajans, japam, ho=\r\nmam etc can help, but they need to be augmented by regular introspection an=\r\nd self-improvement.\n=A0\nTaking mind away from its current pre-occupations (=\r\ne.g. &quot;I am smart&quot;, &quot;I am doing good sadhana&quot;, &quot;I am mad at X&quot;, &quot;I did not g=\r\net what I deserve in Y&quot;, &quot;I am better than X&quot;, &quot;I must have Y at any cost&quot; =\r\netc etc) is key to eventually overcoming conditioning, for these thoughts k=\r\neep *reinforcing* the conditioning!\n=A0\nTo reduce the regular pre-occupatio=\r\nns of mind, different imagery/visualization may work better for some people=\r\n.\n=A0\nOne approach is to contemplate god whenever possible, in the middle o=\r\nf any activity. You can imagine a being in your mind, either as an ideal/ab=\r\nle person or as a principle/ideal/ability that exists in many beings, that =\r\nis so perfect and fascinating for the mind to contemplate that it does not =\r\ncare about other objects around that are making shadripus and ashtapashas w=\r\nork on the mind. Whenever mind is about to entertain its regular debilitati=\r\nng pre-occupations, one can try to contemplate god instead.\n=A0\nMind is a w=\r\nild animal. As Pi says in the movie &quot;Life of Pi&quot; about the tiger on the boa=\r\nt, wild animals can&#39;t be transformed or domesticated, but they can be train=\r\ned into some habits!\n=A0\nWhenever one is enjoying a sensual pleasure, if on=\r\ne thinks &quot;the omnipresent God is enjoying this thru this instrument&quot; and st=\r\narts contemplating the qualities of that god instead of thinking too much a=\r\nbout limited sense objects, one is better placed to reduce the damage done =\r\nby shadripus. Whenever one is angry at someone for what they did, if one th=\r\ninks &quot;the omnipresent God is giving me the fruits of my karmas thru that in=\r\nstrument&quot; and starts contemplating the qualities of that god instead of bei=\r\nng angry at someone, one is better placed to reduce the damage done by shad=\r\nripus. And so on.\n=A0\nIn the beginning, even contemplation of god becomes l=\r\naced with ego. Every now and then, the activity ends up becoming about ones=\r\nelf rather than about god (&quot;*I* am doing this nice bhajan&quot;, &quot;*I* am doing t=\r\nhis nice homam&quot;, &quot;I think *I* am making progress through this&quot;). With effor=\r\nt and perseverance, one can avoid making it about oneself and keep it cente=\r\nred on the supreme power that runs the show. Just as it takes a long time t=\r\no train a wild animal, it takes a long time to train mind!\n=A0\nTry to devel=\r\nop devotion and surrender. Based on all that you read and heard, develop of=\r\n a concept/principle of god that is so superb and fascinarting. Visualize/c=\r\nontemplate that concept as frequently as possible, especially when meditati=\r\nng. When mind veers off into other things, gently steer it back. Don&#39;t spen=\r\nd too much time dissecting what mind is doing and why. Just put it back gen=\r\ntly into contemplating god. Try to make it about god rather than about your=\r\nself.\n=A0\nThe main drawback of the sadhana of most people is that they make=\r\n it about themselves at some level or the other. Though that is unavoidable=\r\n, try to break free from it.\n=A0\n*=A0=A0=A0=A0=A0=A0=A0 *=A0=A0=A0=A0=A0=A0=\r\n=A0 *\n=A0\nFinally, one can try to overcome the limited sense of self and en=\r\ngage in selfless actions that benefit a larger set of people than oneself. =\r\nWhat stops us from truly loving god is our deep and sub-conscious love for =\r\n*ourselves* (i.e. our *limited* notion of self that drives the current body=\r\n-mind complex). One way to overcome that is to selflessly love others. Afte=\r\nr all, other people around us are as much replicas of god as we are. If we =\r\ncannot empathize with them, love them and give them unconditionally, how ca=\r\nn we ever hope to transcend the limited sense of Self and truly love omnipr=\r\nesent God?\n=A0\n\nBest regards,\nNarasimha\n--------\nAstrology & Spirituality R=\r\nesources: http://www.VedicAstrologer.org\n--------\n=A0\n\n&gt;___________________=\r\n_____________\n&gt; From: Leela Sastry &lt;leela.sastry@...&gt;\n&gt;To: &quot;vedic-wis=\r\ndom@yahoogroups.com&quot; &lt;vedic-wisdom@yahoogroups.com&gt; \n&gt;Sent: Thursday, Febru=\r\nary 28, 2013 10:35 PM\n&gt;Subject: Re: [vedic-wisdom] Re: Kundalini syndrome\n&gt;=\r\n \n&gt;\n&gt;=A0 \n&gt;=A0Dear Friends ,\n&gt;=A0All psychosomatic or schizophrenic cases a=\r\nre not defined as=A0=A0=A0 wrongly=A0=A0=A0 experimented=A0=A0kundalini=A0=\r\n=A0 experiences . But some could be=A0 , because=A0 I personally know two t=\r\no three cases .A very=A0=A0intelligent boy who did his masters in BITs -Pil=\r\nani did some=A0 experimenting with that after going through=A0 the material=\r\n=A0about kundalini in the net . He ended=A0 up=A0an incurable case of=A0 so=\r\nme severe psychological disorder . Same=A0 way a lady who did much sadhana =\r\nof Srirama ended up as a case of the same=A0 or similar disorder after some=\r\n time . It is not confirm the point nor=A0 to discourage or encourage the s=\r\nadhana . What is explained=A0 aboutkundalini and the attitude of detachment=\r\n is perfectly correct . But to reach that state is very difficult for all =\r\n=A0and=A0 to start with a guidance is required . To get &#39;that kind of guru =\r\nis also=A0 near impossibility . So it is always desirable to depend on the =\r\nishtadevatha to lead to that stage .When once the\n appropriate time comes e=\r\nven Ishtadevatha also=A0=A0 recedes to the back ground . Of course this is =\r\none view point and=A0=A0 need=A0