n a previous life and may have put enough=\r\n effort. As a result, one may be getting it now. But one may be unprepared =\r\n(and ironically may not even want it!) when it comes in this life.\n&gt;&gt;=A0\n&gt;&gt;=\r\nAs you do sadhana, try not to fancy too many specific desires. Nature has a=\r\n delay mechanism in granting your desires (because of constraints on what\n =\r\nNature can give you right now, arising from YOUR OWN previous actions). So =\r\nNature sometimes gives you what you want LATE, when you no longer want it o=\r\nr want something else. For example, one may pray for great wealth one&#39;s who=\r\nle life and be born as a rich but very sick man in next life. One may not e=\r\nnjoy that wealth and pray whole life for health. In the life after that, on=\r\ne may be very healthy, but not have any knowledge or money. In another case=\r\n, one may deeply desire to act in a famous film. One may be reborn as a tig=\r\ner or a dog and act in a famous film, but not really enjoy that experience.=\r\n Basically, people keep going in circles through various lives, always &quot;see=\r\nking&quot; something they are &quot;missing&quot;.\n&gt;&gt;=A0\n&gt;&gt;Anyway, coming back to Kundalin=\r\ni, if one deeply desires an out of body experience given by a rising Kundal=\r\nini and one&#39;s\n previous karmas constrain one from having it in THIS life, o=\r\nne may be born in next life with this specific desire destined to fructify =\r\n(if there is enough karmik force behind it).\n&gt;&gt;=A0\n&gt;&gt;*=A0=A0=A0=A0=A0=A0=A0=\r\n *=A0=A0=A0=A0=A0=A0=A0 *\n&gt;&gt;=A0\n&gt;&gt;Kundalini rise is not necessarily scary o=\r\nr painful, if one is well-prepared in terms of attitude and detachment.\n&gt;&gt;=\r\n=A0\n&gt;&gt;Once I saw a chipmunk glued to a mouse trap. I went to free it and it=\r\n panicked so badly and started to shake violently. I went to save it from a=\r\n certain slow death and it was scared that I would kill it!\n&gt;&gt;=A0\n&gt;&gt;We are =\r\nlike that chipmunk, glued to the mouse trap called this body-mind complex a=\r\nnd scared of being rescued from a certain slow death!\n&gt;&gt;=A0\n&gt;&gt;If our ideas =\r\nabout who we are (viz this current body-mind complex) are incorrect and if =\r\nwe are this &quot;infinite Self&quot; as shastras say, won&#39;t a complete realization o=\r\nf that at some\n stage involve stepping out of this body-mind complex, witho=\r\nut being scared?\n&gt;&gt;=A0\n&gt;&gt;*=A0=A0=A0=A0=A0=A0=A0 *=A0=A0=A0=A0=A0=A0=A0 *\n&gt;&gt;=\r\n=A0\n&gt;&gt;Kundalini rise after most undesirable conditioning is overcome, is fa=\r\nr better than Kundalini rise forced when some really undesirable conditioni=\r\nng is still left in one&#39;s system.\n&gt;&gt;=A0\n&gt;&gt;When one transcends one problemat=\r\nic notion about who one is and what one needs, another notion that lay buri=\r\ned deeper in consciousness may spring to the surface and torment one. If on=\r\ne overcomes the notion &quot;I am the body&quot;, there may be another notion in one&#39;=\r\ns body-mind complex that one&#39;s awareness clings on to (e.g. a great doctor,=\r\n a great leader, a great scholar, a great saint etc). As an extreme example=\r\n, if one person had a hidden deep desire to be a great soul who rescues the=\r\n world, he may fancy that he is a re-incarnated X or Y who will rescue the =\r\nworld now. When one&#39;s self-awareness (i.e. Kundalini!) deeply clings to any=\r\n such notion, it can cause havoc. The person may show some signs of progres=\r\ns and yet remain in ignorance and get stuck badly.\n&gt;&gt;=A0\n&gt;&gt;An awakened Kund=\r\nalini in a system with undesirable conditioning may accentuate one&#39;s weakne=\r\nsses and wrong notions heavily and cause serious psychiatric and spiritual =\r\nproblems.\n&gt;&gt;=A0\n&gt;&gt;*=A0=A0=A0=A0=A0=A0=A0 *=A0=A0=A0=A0=A0=A0=A0 *\n&gt;&gt;=A0\n&gt;&gt;T=\r\nhe best approach I recommend is to NOT think in terms of Kundalini and its =\r\nrise. Just do sadhana, overcome your weaknesses and improve your detachment=\r\n over time. Again, I want to emphasize that detachment is not disgust or di=\r\nstaste for life/things/people around you. Disgust is the other side of coin=\r\n of attachment. It is a negative attachment. =A0\n&gt;&gt;Don&#39;t worry about whethe=\r\nr your Kundalini rises or not. Worry about whether you are able to resist 6=\r\n internal enemies (shadripus) and 8 bondages (ashta pashas) or not. If your=\r\n ability to resist them is increasing, you are making progress. EVEN IF you=\r\nr Kundalini is fast asleep, you are still making progress. When you complet=\r\nely overcome them, Kundalini (your self-awareness) will automatically ascen=\r\nd to the top and meet Her Lord (true Self).\n&gt;&gt;=A0*=A0=A0=A0=A0=A0=A0=A0 *=\r\n=A0=A0=A0=A0=A0=A0=A0 *\n&gt;&gt;=A0\n&gt;&gt;One word on surrendering to a personal deit=\r\ny. Though true surrender is helpful, most people do not have it. They simpl=\r\ny do business with god. Though people may be offended by my words, this is =\r\nthe plain and bare fact.\n&gt;&gt;=A0\n&gt;&gt;&quot;I want X, I will pray to you and please g=\r\nive it to me&quot;, &quot;I am scared of Kundalini rise, I will pray to you and pleas=\r\ne protect me&quot; - all this is just a business deal. There is something you wa=\r\nnt and you ask god for it. True surrender has no place for agendas, desires=\r\n, demands or expectations. True surrender is losing oneself in one&#39;s fascin=\r\nation for the qualities of Lord. True surrender is accepting anything Lord =\r\nthrows one&#39;s way (whether it is pleasurable or highly painful) as Lord&#39;s pr=\r\nasad and accepting it gratefully. True surrender is thinking of Lord with f=\r\nascination and pleasure, even in the face of (and during) Death.\n&gt;&gt;=A0\n&gt;&gt;If=\r\n one without true surrender and with many desires and wrong notions experie=\r\nnces a Kundalini rise, one may still be trapped, despite thinking of a pers=\r\nonal god. It is not that god does not want to &quot;protect&quot; one as said below. =\r\nIt is not about protecting or endangering. If you go back to my &quot;chipmunk g=\r\nlued to mouse trap&quot; example above, I was trying to protect it, but it was s=\r\ncared. Similarly, one&#39;s conditioning makes one *run away* from God&#39;s protec=\r\ntion! God&#39;s protection may seem to a conditioned mind like grave danger tha=\r\nt\n one should run away from!\n&gt;&gt;=A0\n&gt;&gt;*=A0=A0=A0=A0=A0=A0=A0 *=A0=A0=A0=A0=\r\n=A0=A0=A0 *\n&gt;&gt;=A0\n&gt;&gt;Whether through the path of wisdom or surrender, develo=\r\np dispassion and detachment. Realize that all this is temporary and can be =\r\ntaken away anytime. Enjoy it while you have and keep doing your best, but b=\r\ne prepared to lose everything anytime. Only detachment and a very light men=\r\ntal conditioning (very light desires, dislikes etc) can protect one as one&#39;=\r\ns Kundalini rises to meet True Self. Heavy conditioning and impurities in o=\r\nne&#39;s nadis will distract rising Kundalini (self-awareness) and stop Her fro=\r\nm meeting True Self.\n&gt;&gt;=A0\n&gt;&gt;The real key is how light your conditioning is=\r\n.\n&gt;&gt;=A0\n&gt;&gt;Best regards, Narasimha -------- Astrology & Spirituality Resourc=\r\nes: http://www.vedicastrologer.org/\n&gt;&gt;--------\n&gt;&gt;\n&gt;&gt;=A0\n&gt;&gt;\n&gt;&gt;From: Leela Sa=\r\nstry &lt;leela.sastry@...&gt;\n&gt;&gt;&gt;To: &quot;vedic-wisdom@yahoogroups.com&quot; &lt;vedic-=\r\nwisdom@yahoogroups.com&gt; \n&gt;&gt;&gt;Sent: Thursday, February 28, 2013 6:05 AM\n&gt;&gt;&gt;Su=\r\nbject: Re: [vedic-wisdom] Kundalini syndrome\n&gt;&gt;&gt;\n&gt;&gt;&gt;=A0 \n&gt;&gt;&gt;=A0YES=A0 SIR=\r\n=A0 , perfectly correct=A0=A0 ,=A0but intense bhakthi and saranagathi=A0 ma=\r\nkes the ishtadevatha to stand by the sadhaka and remove most of the hurdles=\r\n .=A0=A0All the so called dhyanamargas with out any personal deity and mant=\r\nhra allow the other entities to enter in to 