n X&quot;, &quot;I must have Y at any cost&quot; e=\r\ntc etc) is key to eventually overcoming conditioning, for\n these thoughts k=\r\neep *reinforcing* the conditioning!&lt;br&gt;&nbsp;&lt;br&gt;To reduce the regular pre-=\r\noccupations of mind, different imagery/visualization may work better for so=\r\nme people.&lt;br&gt;&nbsp;&lt;br&gt;One approach is to contemplate god whenever possibl=\r\ne, in the middle of any activity. You can imagine a being in your mind, eit=\r\nher as an ideal/able person or as a principle/ideal/ability that exists in =\r\nmany beings, that is so perfect and fascinating for the mind to contemplate=\r\n that it does not care about other objects around that are making shadripus=\r\n and ashtapashas work on the mind. Whenever mind is about to entertain its =\r\nregular debilitating pre-occupations, one can try to contemplate god instea=\r\nd.&lt;br&gt;&nbsp;&lt;br&gt;Mind is a wild animal. As Pi says in the movie &quot;Life of Pi&quot;=\r\n about the tiger on the boat, wild animals can&#39;t be transformed or domestic=\r\nated, but they can be trained into some habits!&lt;br&gt;&nbsp;&lt;br&gt;Whenever one i=\r\ns enjoying a sensual pleasure, if one thinks &quot;the\n omnipresent God is enjoy=\r\ning this thru this instrument&quot; and starts contemplating the qualities of th=\r\nat god instead of thinking too much about limited sense objects, one is bet=\r\nter placed to reduce the damage done by shadripus. Whenever one is angry at=\r\n someone for what they did, if one thinks &quot;the omnipresent God is giving me=\r\n the fruits of my karmas thru that instrument&quot; and starts contemplating the=\r\n qualities of that god instead of being angry at someone, one is better pla=\r\nced to reduce the damage done by shadripus. And so on.&lt;br&gt;&nbsp;&lt;br&gt;In the =\r\nbeginning, even contemplation of god becomes laced with ego. Every now and =\r\nthen, the activity ends up becoming about oneself rather than about god (&quot;*=\r\nI* am doing this nice bhajan&quot;, &quot;*I* am doing this nice homam&quot;, &quot;I think *I*=\r\n am making progress through this&quot;). With effort and perseverance, one can a=\r\nvoid making it about oneself and keep it centered on the supreme power that=\r\n runs the show. Just as it takes a long\n time to train a wild animal, it ta=\r\nkes a long time to train mind!&lt;br&gt;&nbsp;&lt;br&gt;Try to develop devotion and sur=\r\nrender. Based on all that you read and heard, develop of a concept/principl=\r\ne of god that is so superb and fascinarting. Visualize/contemplate that con=\r\ncept as frequently as possible, especially when meditating. When mind veers=\r\n off into other things, gently steer it back. Don&#39;t spend too much time dis=\r\nsecting what mind is doing and why. Just put it back gently into contemplat=\r\ning god. Try to make it about god rather than about yourself.&lt;br&gt;&nbsp;&lt;br&gt;=\r\nThe main drawback of the sadhana of most people is that they make it about =\r\nthemselves at some level or the other. Though that is unavoidable, try to b=\r\nreak free from it.&lt;br&gt;&nbsp;&lt;br&gt;*&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;=\r\n *&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; *&lt;br&gt;&nbsp;&lt;br&gt;Finally, one ca=\r\nn try to overcome the limited sense of self and engage in selfless actions =\r\nthat benefit a larger set of\n people than oneself. What stops us from truly=\r\n loving god is our deep and sub-conscious love for *ourselves* (i.e. our *l=\r\nimited* notion of self that drives the current body-mind complex). One way =\r\nto overcome that is to selflessly love others. After all, other people arou=\r\nnd us are as much replicas of god as we are. If we cannot empathize with th=\r\nem, love them and give them unconditionally, how can we ever hope to transc=\r\nend the limited sense of Self and truly love omnipresent God?&lt;br&gt;&nbsp;&lt;br&gt;=\r\n&lt;div style=3D&quot;color:rgb(0, 0, 0);font-size:13px;font-family:arial